### HMS Ward Service API Collection
### Port: 3006 | Base URL: http://localhost:3006
### Auth: Bearer token via Keycloak

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3006
@keycloakUrl = http://localhost:8080
@realm = hms
@clientId = hms-backend
@clientSecret = your-client-secret

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 0. GET ACCESS TOKEN
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 0. Get Access Token (Keycloak)
# @name getToken
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&client_secret={{clientSecret}}&username=admin&password=admin

### Auth token (auto-filled after step 0)
@adminToken = {{getToken.response.body.access_token}}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WARDS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. List All Wards (with occupancy counts)
GET {{baseUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 2. List Active Wards Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/wards?is_active=true
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 3. Filter Wards by Type (ICU)
GET {{baseUrl}}/wards?type=icu
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 4. Create Male General Ward
# @name createMaleWard
POST {{baseUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Male General Ward",
  "type": "general",
  "capacity": 20
}

### Male Ward ID
@maleWardId = {{createMaleWard.response.body.data.id}}

###

### 5. Create Female General Ward
# @name createFemaleWard
POST {{baseUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Female General Ward",
  "type": "general",
  "capacity": 15
}

### Female Ward ID
@femaleWardId = {{createFemaleWard.response.body.data.id}}

###

### 6. Create ICU Ward
# @name createIcuWard
POST {{baseUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "ICU",
  "type": "icu",
  "capacity": 6
}

###

### 7. Create Private Ward
POST {{baseUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Private Ward",
  "type": "private",
  "capacity": 8
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BEDS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 8. List All Beds
GET {{baseUrl}}/beds
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 9. List Beds in Male General Ward
GET {{baseUrl}}/beds?ward_id={{maleWardId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 10. List Available Beds Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/beds?status=available
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 11. List Available Beds in Male Ward
GET {{baseUrl}}/beds?ward_id={{maleWardId}}&status=available
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 12. Get First Available Bed ID (for testing)
# Run GET /beds?ward_id={{maleWardId}}&status=available and copy an ID here
@bedId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

###

### 13. Set Bed to Maintenance
PUT {{baseUrl}}/beds/{{bedId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "maintenance",
  "notes": "Bed frame broken — awaiting repair"
}

###

### 14. Set Bed Back to Available
PUT {{baseUrl}}/beds/{{bedId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "available"
}

###

### 15. Set Bed to Reserved
PUT {{baseUrl}}/beds/{{bedId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "reserved",
  "notes": "Reserved for expected post-op patient"
}

###

### 16. Try to Set Bed to Occupied (should fail with 422)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/beds/{{bedId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "occupied"
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMISSIONS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 17. Admit Patient 1 (Andrea Lalema)
# @name admitPatient1
# First set the bedId to an available bed from step 11
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "patientName": "Andrea Lalema",
  "patientNumber": "R00001",
  "bedId": "{{bedId}}",
  "attendingDoctorId": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
  "attendingDoctorName": "Dr. Jenny Smith",
  "admissionReason": "High fever with suspected typhoid — IV treatment required",
  "notes": "Allergic to Penicillin"
}

### Admission 1 ID
@admission1Id = {{admitPatient1.response.body.data.id}}

###

### 18. Try to Admit Same Patient Again (should fail with 422 PATIENT_ALREADY_ADMITTED)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "patientName": "Andrea Lalema",
  "bedId": "{{bedId}}",
  "attendingDoctorId": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
  "admissionReason": "Second attempt — should be rejected"
}

###

### 19. Admit Patient 2 to a Different Bed
# @name admitPatient2
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333",
  "patientName": "John Fernando",
  "patientNumber": "R00042",
  "bedId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
  "attendingDoctorId": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
  "attendingDoctorName": "Dr. Jenny Smith",
  "admissionReason": "Post-operative recovery after appendectomy"
}

### Admission 2 ID
@admission2Id = {{admitPatient2.response.body.data.id}}

###

### 20. List All Current Admissions (admitted)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions?status=admitted
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 21. List Admissions by Ward
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions?ward_id={{maleWardId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 22. List Admissions by Doctor
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions?attending_doctor_id=22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 23. List Admissions with Date Range
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions?from=2026-01-01&to=2026-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 24. List Discharged Admissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions?status=discharged
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 25. Get Admission by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 26. Get Non-Existent Admission (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WARD SERVICE CHARGES (charge stacking during admission)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 27. Add Daily Bed Charge (Day 1)
# @name addBedCharge1
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: ward_staff

{
  "serviceName": "Daily Bed Charge",
  "serviceType": "bed_charge",
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 2500.00,
  "notes": "Day 1"
}

### Service ID
@service1Id = {{addBedCharge1.response.body.data.id}}

###

### 28. Add Medication Charge
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: doctor

{
  "serviceName": "IV Ceftriaxone 1g",
  "serviceType": "medication",
  "quantity": 2,
  "unitPrice": 450.00,
  "notes": "Twice daily x 5 days"
}

###

### 29. Add Another Daily Bed Charge (Day 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: ward_staff

{
  "serviceName": "Daily Bed Charge",
  "serviceType": "bed_charge",
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 2500.00,
  "notes": "Day 2"
}

###

### 30. Add Procedure Charge
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: doctor

{
  "serviceName": "Blood Transfusion",
  "serviceType": "procedure",
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 2550.00
}

###

### 31. Add Investigation Charge
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: ward_staff

{
  "serviceName": "Full Blood Count",
  "serviceType": "investigation",
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 750.00
}

###

### 32. Add Meal Charge
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: ward_staff

{
  "serviceName": "Hospital Meals (3 days)",
  "serviceType": "meal",
  "quantity": 3,
  "unitPrice": 500.00
}

###

### 33. Get All Services for Admission (running total)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 34. Filter Services by Type (medications only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services?service_type=medication
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 35. Get Admission Detail with Services and Running Total
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 36. Remove a Service Charge (undo incorrect entry)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services/{{service1Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 37. Add Bed Charge Back (replacement)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Name: ward_staff

{
  "serviceName": "Daily Bed Charge",
  "serviceType": "bed_charge",
  "quantity": 3,
  "unitPrice": 2500.00,
  "notes": "3 days total"
}

###

### 38. Try to Add Service to Discharged Admission (should fail 422)
# (Run this after step 39 discharge)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/services
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceName": "Post-discharge test",
  "serviceType": "other",
  "quantity": 1,
  "unitPrice": 100.00
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DISCHARGE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 39. Discharge Patient 1 (publishes billing.ward event to Finance)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/discharge
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dischargeNotes": "Patient recovered well. Discharge with oral antibiotics x 7 days.",
  "dischargeDiagnosis": "Typhoid Fever — resolved with IV Ceftriaxone"
}

###

### 40. Verify Bed is Available Again (after discharge)
GET {{baseUrl}}/beds?ward_id={{maleWardId}}&status=available
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 41. Try to Discharge Again (should fail with ALREADY_DISCHARGED 422)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}/discharge
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dischargeNotes": "Second attempt — should fail"
}

###

### 42. Get Discharged Admission Details (final_total included)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission1Id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PATIENT ADMISSION HISTORY
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 43. Get Patient 1 Full Admission History
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 44. Get Patient 1 History — Paginated
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/admissions?page=1&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 45. Get Patient with No History
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999999/admissions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WARD OVERVIEW (after discharge — verify counts updated)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 46. Final Ward Overview — check occupancy updated
GET {{baseUrl}}/wards
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 47. Discharge Without Body (body is optional)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admissions/{{admission2Id}}/discharge
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###
